<footer>
  Source: Salesforce, May 11, 2026. Active sellers only (Owner.IsActive = true). Closed won and open pipe figures cover 2026 YTD. Avg cycle and close-won rate use combined 2025+2026 closures plus current open opps. Currency converted to USD at mid-market rates (not finance-grade).
  <br><br>
  <b>Acquisition (Acq)</b> = New Practice + Reactivate Practice opportunity types. <b>Acq stalled</b> = open Acq opportunity with no stage change in 60+ days. For reference, 90% of NP wins close in under 35 days. The aging strip splits ALL open opps into 0–30d (fresh), 30–60d (warming), 60–90d (stalled), 90d+ (severely stalled). <b>Stage</b> bar shows Discover → Consult → Close → Order Form Sent → Order Form Viewed.
  <br><br>
  <b>Avg cycle</b> = mean days between CreatedDate and CloseDate for combined 2025+2026 closed-won opportunities. <b>Close-won rate</b> = won / (won + lost + open) across all the seller's opportunities. Open opportunities count against the rate because they haven't converted yet — when they do close, they shift the rate accordingly. This makes pipe hygiene (advancing or killing dead deals) directly visible in the seller's number.
</footer>

